 Origenes seine einzig dastehende Exegese mit der oft angegriffenen allegorischen Auslegungsmethode an.  aOrigen’s work is mainly preserved only in fragments, as he was condemned as a heretic after his death. Thus only a fraction of his commentary on Genesis is still in existence, albeit a relatively large portion of the work and one of particular significance, as the story of the Creation is used to treat major themes in cosmology and views of destiny. Fragments of the history of the Patriarchs provide examples of Origen’s idiosyncratic hermeneutics in its allegorical and psychological interpretation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn Greek, Modern (1453â€“).0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aCreationism. 4aAltes Testament. 4aExegese. 4aGenesis. 4aHermeneutik. 4aOrigenes. 7aRELIGION / Christian Theology / History.2bisacsh  aExegesis.  aGenesis.  aHermeneutics.  aOld Testament.1 aMetzler, Karin, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Theology and Religious Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110638165oZDB-23-GTR08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2009z9783110219517oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET THEOLOGIE/RELIGIONSWISS./JUDAISTIK  2009z9783110219494oZDB-23-DGF0 cprintz978311019344240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311021508340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110215083423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110215083/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGFb2009  aZDB-23-DGGb2009  aZDB-23-GTRc2000d2014